text: Dinslaken is a town in Wesel in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. It is known for its harness racing track, its now closed coal mine in Lohberg, and its wealthy neighborhoods Hiesfeld and Eppinghoven. About 67,000 live in Dinslaken. It is in the Ruhr Area. == Districts == Dinslaken has 7 districts: * Eppinghoven * Hiesfeld * Innenstadt * Lohberg * Oberlohberg * Bruch * Averbruch * Hagenbezirk == References == ==Other websites== Category:Wesel (district)
